Done. Both required files are emitted in the bundle directory and the transcript validates against `transcript_schema.json` (10 iterations, 40 hypotheses, 40 analyses).

Key findings across the 10 iterations:
- **Pembrolizumab** has a small overall ORR benefit (+1pp, p=3e-3) that is concentrated in PD-L1-high (interaction p=5e-11), TMB-high (p=4e-4), and STK11-WT (p=2e-3) tumors; a 3-way pembro × PD-L1-hi × STK11 interaction (p=0.049) shows STK11 mutation eliminates the PD-L1-hi benefit.
- **Matched targeted therapies** (osimertinib/EGFR, sotorasib/KRAS-G12C, olaparib/BRCA2) showed **no** significant biomarker × treatment interactions — the most striking negative finding.
- **Classical prognostics** dominate: ECOG (p=1.7e-93), stage IV (p=1e-33), brain mets (p=2e-18), weight loss (p=2e-32), albumin (+), CRP (–), sex_female (+).
- No SNP survives Bonferroni; comorbidities largely uninformative; only modest insurance disparity (private > medicaid, p=0.04); pembrolizumab assignment balanced across race/insurance.
